725136f-a.text:
24th Drive (foreground, not shown), between 19th and 21st Streets, showing in the foreground Emily P. Woolsey's gardener's cottage. In the background is Mallison's Silk Mill facing Twenty-fourth Ave.
1922.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection.

725137f-a.text:
24th Drive, west from 21st Street to 19th Street and Astoria Park, showing new homes in Astoria. En the background
is the Hellgate Bridge.
Ewing Galloway  About 1927

725140f-a.title: Queens: 24th Terrace - 19th Street
725140f-a.text:
244th Terrace, south side, east from 19th to 21st Streets, showing the demolition of brick homes for the construction of the Triborough Bridge. 24th Terrace, a one-block thoroughfare formerly called Park Terrace, was obliterated when the bridge was constructed.
P. L. Sperr  May 27, 1934
